<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n56127b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n56" href="#n56127b">N56 (VI.B.41)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n56all.htm#n56127b"> 127(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> prudent than crow ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A hero is <mark>more prudent than the crow</mark>, a better guide than the Kat&aacute; grouse, more generous than the cock, warier than the crane, braver than the lion, more aggressive than the panther, finer-sighted than the horse, craftier than the fox, greedier than the gazelle, more vigilant than the dog, and thriftier than the ant. <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE4" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE4"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 170</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
